# SA Cricket App

## Stack
- Expo Router with TypeScript
- Supabase for backend (auth, database, realtime)
- React Native functional components only — no class components

## Project structure
- `app/` — Expo Router screens and layouts
- `app/(tabs)/` — bottom tab navigation (Home, Teams, Stats)
- `components/` — reusable UI components
- `lib/` — shared utilities and clients (e.g. Supabase)
- `constants/` — static data and configuration

## Conventions
- Use functional components with typed props
- Use `@/` path alias for imports
- Fetch live data from Supabase; keep sample/placeholder data only for development
- Environment variables: `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`

## SA Cricket Teams
The app covers South African domestic and national cricket:
- Proteas (national team)
- Titans
- Lions
- Dolphins
- Cape Cobras
- Knights
- Warriors

Team data lives in `constants/teams.ts`.
